Subject: [PATCH] flist templates: emit ${VAR} not $(VAR); teach lint parser ${}

Repo:  nanosoc_gen  (submodule: nanosoc_arch_tech/nanosoc_gen)
Apply: from the nanosoc_gen repo root:  git apply 0002-...patch
       (or:  patch -p1 < 0002-...patch)
Then:  regenerate the golden snapshots (see "REQUIRED FOLLOW-UP" below).

WHY
---
nanosoc_gen renders per-module filelists from Jinja templates that write
Makefile-style $(VAR) paths. VCS expands ${VAR} and $VAR but NOT $(VAR) -- it
treats a $(VAR) path as a literal and fails with Error-[SFCOR]. Downstream the
nanosoc-ethernet-chiplet superproject carries flist/flatten_soc_flist.py purely
to rewrite $(VAR) -> ${VAR} on the generated flists before VCS sees them. Fixing
the templates removes the reason that shim exists.

Three flist templates emit $(VAR):
  soc_model/backends/templates/soc_toplevel.flist.j2
  soc_model/backends/templates/ahb_interconnect.flist.j2
  soc_model/backends/templates/perf_probe.flist.j2

This patch converts $(VAR) -> ${VAR} in all three, and updates the ONE internal
consumer that parsed the old syntax.

IS IT SAFE TO APPLY DIRECTLY?  -- Yes for real tools, but it is a COORDINATED
change, not an isolated template edit. Blast radius:

 1. lint.py (soc_model/backends/lint.py) is nanosoc_gen's OWN flist parser. Its
    _expand_vars regex matched ONLY $(VAR):  re.sub(r'\$\((\w+)\)', ...). Left
    alone, ${VAR} paths would pass through unexpanded and every source file would
    read as "not found". This patch widens the regex to accept BOTH $(VAR) and
    ${VAR}, so it keeps working for any hand-written flist that still uses $(...).
    (Included in this patch.)

 2. Golden snapshot byte-match tests (tests/golden/test_flists.py, FL-01/FL-04 and
    the perf-probe backend test) compare rendered output against checked-in
    __snapshots__/*/*_toplevel.flist and *_interconnect.flist that contain $(...).
    They WILL fail until regenerated. This is mechanical, not a real regression.
    (See REQUIRED FOLLOW-UP.)

 3. GNU Make treats $(VAR) and ${VAR} as identical, so any Makefile-based consumer
    that `include`s or word-expands these flists is UNAFFECTED. No consumer relies
    on the $(...) spelling specifically -- the only tools that care (VCS, shells)
    strictly PREFER ${...}.

 4. NOT TOUCHED, on purpose: tb_Makefile.j2 and firmware_memmap.mk.j2 also emit
    $(VAR), but those are genuine GNU Makefiles where $(VAR) is correct. This
    patch is scoped to the three *.flist.j2 templates only.

This affects EVERY nanosoc_gen downstream (single-core nanosoc, eth-ss, the
chiplet SoC) because the templates are shared -- which is the point: fix it once,
upstream, and delete flatten_soc_flist.py's rewrite step.

REQUIRED FOLLOW-UP (same commit)
--------------------------------
  pytest tests/golden/test_flists.py --snapshot-update
  pytest tests/test_perf_probe_backend.py            # regen its inline flist expectation if snapshotted
  # then re-run the suite to confirm green:
  pytest tests/golden/test_flists.py

